private properties

arrow function:
Arrow function is used to define anonymous function.
It is also called lambda function.
ES6 supports arrow function.

syntax: (par1, par2, par3,...) => {expression};

ES5:

var getResult=function(userName,points){
    return username +" "+points; 
}



Es6:

var getResult:(userName:string, points:number):string=>{
    return userName + " "+points;
}



